review_blob: Unbelievable chocolate bomb! Great aftertaste that lingers.Alcohol well hidden.One of the great stouts! Sit back put your headphones on and enjoy on a cool fall night! You might not get out of your chair!
Will not drink a better DIPA! Piney GRAPEFRUIT BOMB! The best I have had from this series.Way up there with Pliny and Sucks!
Absolutely the best! Coffee bomb! I have tasted the mecca of stouts! Wow.Scour the Earth for this one!Can I give it better than 100!
Hops on Hops! Resin,floral abound! Major after taste.Dry hops.Overall a great IPA!
Love this wonderful nutty ,malty old ale.Perfect ale for late fall into the winter.Great escape from the crazy piney hoppy IPAs I adore.

At first taste I am thinking what is all the hype about.But as I savour this ale I realize I am comparing it to Jubilation,Hibernation and Anchor Steam XMAS ales.This beer is unique.Cinnamon and honey abounds.Not real malty and leaves a nice after taste.Something different for the Holidays! Enjoy.I am.
Awesome! Wish it was available year round.Citrus abounds.Best IPA that Founders has done1
What happen  this year? The hoppy resonous bomb from 2011 is missing.This is likes the Sierra Nevada Pale Ale bottled as Celebration Ale.

beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Double Wide I.P.A.

review_blob: Decent IPA.Lacked piny and hoppy aroma.Dry finish.Better straight from can.I prefer Westbrook IPA.
Like drinking fall.Hint of nutmeg and spices.One of my favorite seasonal beers.Extra alcohol well hidden.Exceptional!
On tap at Carolina Ale House in Greenville SC.Nice resinous floral hops.One of my old favorites.Better than 420.

beer_name: New Belgium / Alpine Lips of Faith - Super India Pale Ale

review_blob: Incredible burst of hops! Piny,resinous.Had several bombers.The 10 percent ABV well hidden. One of the best IPAs I have ever had!Total wine in Greenville SC and Greenes in Greenville had bombers.I bought them out!
